{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8ba550a4-bd6b-4c82-b066-7af2d3aca5c0","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n**In the `.csproj`:**\n1. Remove the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. Add the unified `MSTest` v3 NuGet package (replaces both `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter`)\n3. Update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\n**Your test code is fine** — MSTest v3 uses the same namespace and attributes (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `Assert.*`, etc.).\n\nWant me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b3fac156-638c-4cbd-a651-c0d1d13422c2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n1. A .NET Framework 4.6.2 project (`net462`)\n2. An old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n3. `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` 17.5.0\n4. Test code using `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3, they need to:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` NuGet package (v3.x) which is the unified package for MSTest v3 (replaces the old `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` combo)\n\n\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a version compatible with MSTest v3, and they could optionally bump the target framework from net462 to something newer like net8.0+ if they want, though net462 is still supported.\n\nThe nice part is that the `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace and all the test attributes and assertions stay the same, so their existing test code won't need any modifications.","outputTokens":480,"requestId":"0C00:3B8D06:6C08F85:7541DA5:69F01C58"},"id":"5df191a7-f612-4811-b26f-22e3e8e3b506","timestamp":"2026-04-28T02:33:07.154Z","parentId":"eca7b3ba-f418-486b-9617-b2762450b5e7"}
